y%20Deny%20Defend%3A%20Why%20Insurance%20Companies%20Don't%20Pay%20Claims%20and%20What%20You%20Can%20Do%20About%20It%2C%26quot%3B%20causing%20speculation%20that%20the%20shooter%20may%20have%20been%20referring%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bdelay%2C%20deny%2C%20defend%26quot%3B%20is%20also%20common%20among%20lawyers%20who%20say%20that%20insurance%20companies%20delay%20the%20claims%20process%20with%20paperwork%2C%20deny%20claims%20that%20should%20be%20covered%2C%20and%20then%20defend%20themselves%20in%20court%20if%20a%20claimant%20pursues%20legal%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suspect%20of%20Thompson's%20shooting%20was%20still%20on%20the%20run%20as%20of%20Friday%20afternoon.%20Police%20haven't%20shared%20a%20motive%20behind%20the%20killing%2C%20which%20took%20place%20Wednesday%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeinman%2C%20an%20author%20and%20professor%20emeritus%20at%20Rutgers%2C%20wrote%20about%C2%A0the%20insurance%20industry's%20evolution%20and%20shared%20advice%20for%20consumers%20on%20handling%20disputed%20claims%20in%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BDelay%20Deny%20Defend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20NYPD%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20comment%20when%20asked%20if%20police%20were%20investigating%20any%20link%20between%20the%20book%20and%20the%20shooting.%20The%20author%20also%20declined%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20of%20the%20key%20takeaways%20from%20Feinman's%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a20be4a6-8e63-4201-875a-0585491ce4e1%5C%22%3EThere's%20only%20one%20mention%20of%20UnitedHealthcare%20by%20name.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Feinman%20mentioned%20several%20top%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrian-thompsons-fatal-shooting-industry-leaders-react-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsurance%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20name%20throughout%20the%20book%20%E2%80%94%20State%20Farm%20and%20Allstate%20in%20particular%20%E2%80%94%20UnitedHealthcare%20only%20appeared%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20introduction%2C%20Feinman%20described%20how%2C%20in%202009%2C%20UnitedHealth%2C%20Aetna%2C%20Guardian%2C%20and%20other%20companies%20agreed%20to%20stop%20using%20certain%20databases%20to%20calculate%20fees%20for%20out-of-network%20treatment%20after%20being%20accused%20by%20then-New%20York%20Attorney%20General%20Andrew%20Cuomo%20of%20systematically%20lowballing%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221e191562-bc17-483c-abc1-c0983d1d21d3%5C%22%3EFeinman%20says%20the%20insurance%20industry%20changed%20in%20the%20early%201990s.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdelaydenydefend.com%2Fexcerpt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintro%20to%20his%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Feinman%20wrote%20that%20insurance%20companies%20began%20to%20significantly%20reconsider%20the%20claims%20process%20in%20the%201990s%20when%20they%20%26quot%3Bbecame%20a%20profit%20center%20rather%20than%20the%20place%20that%20kept%20the%20company's%20promise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20part%20of%20this%20shift%20occurred%20when%20insurance%20companies%2C%20including%20Allstate%20in%201992%2C%20hired%20consulting%20giant%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinsey%20developed%20new%20strategies%20for%20handling%20claims%20and%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bzero-sum%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20Feinman%20writes.%20The%20insurance%20companies%20started%20using%20computer%20systems%20to%20estimate%20the%20amounts%20to%20be%20paid%20and%20deterring%20claimants%20from%20hiring%20lawyers%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinsey%20declined%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22597d2c60-eb0f-42e7-b9ad-65867019ce7d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsurance%20companies%20aren't%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20also%20not%20the%20enemy%2C%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFeinman%20said%20in%20the%20book%20that%20insurance%20companies%20aren't%20our%20friends