idia%20in%20any%20way%2C%20shape%2C%20or%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20you%20want%20to%20see%20Nvidia's%20use%20case%20increase%20on%20AWS%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20customers%20believe%20that's%20the%20way%20they%20need%20to%20go%2C%20then%20they'll%20do%20it.%20Of%20course%2C%20if%20it's%20good%20for%20customers%2C%20it's%20good%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20is%20very%20big%2C%20so%20there's%20room%20for%20multiple%20vendors%20here.%20We're%20not%20forcing%20anybody%20to%20use%20those%20chips%2C%20but%20we're%20working%20very%20hard%20to%20ensure%20that%20our%20major%20tenets%2C%20which%20are%20high%20performance%20and%20lower%20cost%2C%20will%20materialize%20to%20benefit%20our%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoes%20it%20mean%20AWS%20is%20OK%20being%20in%20second%20place%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20competition.%20There's%20no%20machine-learning%20award%20ceremony%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20a%20customer%20like%20Anthropic%2C%20there's%20very%20clear%20scientific%20evidence%20that%20larger%20compute%20infrastructure%20allows%20you%20to%20build%20larger%20models%20with%20more%20data.%20And%20if%20you%20do%20that%2C%20you%20get%20higher%20accuracy%20and%20more%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20ability%20to%20scale%20capacity%20to%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20Trainium%202%20chips%20gives%20them%20the%20opportunity%20to%20innovate%20on%20something%20they%20couldn't%20have%20done%20before.%20They%20get%20a%205x%20boost%20in%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20being%20No.%201%20important%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20is%20big%20enough.%20No.%202%20is%20a%20very%20good%20position%20to%20be%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20saying%20I'm%20No.%202%20or%20No.%201%2C%20by%20the%20way.%20But%20it's%20really%20not%20something%20I'm%20even%20thinking%20about.%20We're%20so%20early%20in%20our%20journey%20here%20in%20machine%20learning%20in%20general%2C%20the%20industry%20in%20general%2C%20and%20also%20on%20the%20chips%20specifically%2C%20we're%20just%20heads%20down%20serving%20customers%20like%20Anthropic%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20all%20the%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20not%20even%20doing%20competitive%20analysis%20with%20Nvidia.%20I'm%20not%20running%20benchmarks%20against%20Nvidia.%20I%20don't%20need%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmlcommons.org%2Fbenchmarks%2Ftraining%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMLPerf%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20industry%20performance%20benchmark.%20Companies%20that%20participate%20in%20MLPerf%20have%20performance%20engineers%20working%20just%20to%20improve%20MLPerf%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20completely%20a%20distraction%20for%20us.%20We're%20not%20participating%20in%20that%20because%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20waste%20time%20on%20a%20benchmark%20that%20isn't%20customer-focused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20surface%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20helping%20companies%20grow%20on%20AWS%20isn't%20always%20beneficial%20for%20AWS's%20own%20products%20because%20you're%20competing%20with%20them.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20the%20same%20company%20that%20is%20the%20best%20place%20Netflix%20is%20running%20on%2C%20and%20we%20also%20have%20Prime%20Video.%20It's%20part%20of%20our%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20say%20that%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20customers%20that%20are%20still%20on%20GPUs.%20A%20lot%20of%20customers%20love%20GPUs%2C%20and%20they%20have%20no%20intention%20to%20move%20to%20Trainium%20anytime%20soon.%20And%20that's%20fine%2C%20because%2C%20again%2C%20we're%20giving%20them%20the%20options%20and%20they%20decide%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20see%20these%20AI%20tools%20becoming%20more%20commoditized%20in%20the%20future%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20hope%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20started%20this%20in%202016%2C%20the%20problem%20was%20that%20there%20was%20no%20operating%20system%20for%20machine%20learning.%20So%20we%20really%20had%20to%20invent%20all%20the%20tools%20that%20go%20around%20these%20chips%20to%20make%20them%20work%20for%20our%20customers%20as%20seamlessly%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20machine%20learning%20becomes%20commoditized%20on%20the%20software%20and%20hardware%20sides%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20everybody.%20It%20means%20that%20it's%20easier%20to%20use%20those%20solutions.%20But%20running%20machine%20learning%20meaningfully%20is%20still%20an%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20some%20of%20the%20different%20types%20of%20workloads%20customers%20might%20want%20to%20run%20on%20GPUs%20versus%20Trainium%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGPUs%20are%20more%20of%20a%20general-purpose%20processor%20of%20machine%20learning.%20All%20the%20researchers%20and%20data%20scientists%20in%20the%20world%20know%20how%20to%20use%20Nvidia%20pretty%20well.%20If%20you%20invent%20something%20new%2C%20if%20you%20do%20that%20on%20GPU%2C%20then%20things%20will%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20invent%20something%20new%20on%20specialized%20chips%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20either%20ensure%20compiler%20technology%20understands%20what%20you%20just%20built%20or%20create%20your%20own%20compute%20kernel%20for%20that%20workload.%20We're%20focused%20mainly%20on%20use%20cases%20where%20our%20customers%20tell%20us%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20this%20is%20what%20we%20need.%26quot%3B%20Usually%20the%20customers%20we%20get%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20seeing%20increased%20costs%20as%20an%20issue%20and%20are%20trying%20to%20look%20for%20alternatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20the%20most%20advanced%20workloads%20are%20usually%20reserved%20for%20Nvidia%20chips%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsually.%20If%20data-science%20folks%20need%20to%20continuously%20run%20experiments%2C%20they'll%20probably%20do%20that%20on%20a%20GPU%20cluster.%20When%20they%20know%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%2C%20that's%20where%20they%20have%20more%20options.%20That's%20where%20Trainium%20really%20shines%2C%20because%20it%20gives%20high%20performance%20at%20a%20lower%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAWS%20CEO%20Matt%20Garman%20previously%20said%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20workloads%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20on%20Nvidia.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20sense.%20We%20give%20value%20to%20customers%20who%20have%20a%20large%20spend%20and%20are%20trying%20to%20see%20how%20they%20can%20control%20the%20costs%20a%20bit%20better.%20When%20Matt%20says%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20workloads%2C%20it%20means%20medical%20imaging%2C%20speech%20recognition%2C%20weather%20forecasting%2C%20and%20all%20sorts%20of%20workloads%20that%20we're%20not%20really%20focused%20on%20right%20now%20because%20we%20have%20large%20customers%20who%20ask%20us%20to%20do%20bigger%20things.%20So%20that%20statement%20is%20100%25%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20nutshell%2C%20we%20want%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20the%20best%20place%20for%20GPUs%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20Trainium%20when%20customers%20need%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20has%20Anthropic%20done%20to%20help%20AWS%20in%20the%20AI%20space%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20very%20strong%20opinions%20of%20what%20they%20need%2C%20and%20they%20come%20back%20to%20us%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20can%20we%20add%20feature%20A%20to%20your%20future%20chip%3F%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20dialogue.%20Some%20ideas%20they%20came%20up%20with%20weren't%20feasible%20to%20even%20implement%20in%20a%20piece%20of%20silicon.%20We%20actually%20implemented%20some%20ideas%2C%20and%20for%20others%20we%20came%20back%20with%20a%20better%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20they're%20such%20experts%20in%20building%20foundation%20models%2C%20this%20really%20helps%20us%20home%20in%20on%20building%20chips%20that%20are%20really%20good%20at%20what%20they%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20just%20announced%20Project%20Rainier%20together.%20Thi