he%20Office%20for%20National%20Statistics%20or%20ONS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20staff%20at%20Great%20Britain's%20statistical%20office%20has%20in-fact%20been%20observing%20the%20trend%20for%20a%20while%20now.%20Jotting%20down%20the%20most%20popular%20names%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20besides%20other%20important%20statistics%2C%20it%20revealed%20that%20Muhammad%20has%20been%20among%20the%20top%2010%20names%20for%20baby%20boys%20since%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdding%20to%20the%20cheer%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Statistics%20said%20that%20other%20spellings%20of%20the%20name%20Muhammad%20-%20namely%20Mohammed%20and%20Mohammad%20-%20also%20made%20the%20top%20100%20list%20for%20England%20and%20Wales.%20This%2C%20the%20ONS%20explained%2C%20is%20because%20it%20considers%20each%20spelling%20as%20a%20separate%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVictoria%2C%20Harry%2C%20William%2C%20and%20Charlotte%20are%20no%20longer%20popular%20names%20for%20children%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20the%20data%20showed%2C%20adding%20that%20Elizabeth%20and%20Charles%20are%20also%20not%20a%20favourite%20among%20young%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nine%20other%20top%20names%20for%20newborn%20boys%20in%20Britain%20are%20-%20Noah%2C%20Oliver%2C%20George%2C%20Leo%2C%20Arthur%2C%20Luca%2C%20Theodore%2C%20Oscar%2C%20and%20Henry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20newborn%20girls%2C%20the%20ten%20most%20popular%20names%20in%20Britain%20in%202023%20were%20-%20Olivia%2C%20Amelia%2C%20Isla%2C%20Lily%2C%20Freya%2C%20Ava%2C%20Ivy%2C%20Florence%2C%20Willow%2C%20and%20Isabella.%20The%20top%20three%20names%20for%20girls%20have%20remained%20unchanged%20for%20a%20third%20consecutive%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statistical%20office%20also%20said%20that%20new%20entries%20to%20the%20list%20of%20top%20100%20baby%20names%20include%20Hazel%2C%20Lilah%2C%20Autumn%2C%20Nevaeh%20and%20Raya%20for%20girls%2C%20and%20Jax%2C%20Enzo%2C%20and%20Bodhi%20for%20boys.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20noted%20that%20the%20time%20of%20year%2